What are ANGOSTURA® bitters? How do you use them? Where did they come from? And what's up with that iconic oversized bottle label? 

We answer all these questions and more in this Bitters 101 lesson with Greg Titian of @How2Drink. Watch him dash his way through the history, purpose and power of ANGOSTURA® bitters – a bartender's salt and pepper.

This one is for the tequila lovers who are tired of margaritas. Spice up your Happy Hour routine with this refreshing twist on a Calvados Pucker. Using ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters to add spice and Green Chartreuse for an herbal flair, this tequila cocktail is a complex palate pleaser that's ideal for summertime sipping in between great socializating and conversations. Swipe for the recipe specs.

CC: @idealistfoods 

Silver Apple Recipe:
1 1/2 oz Tequila Plata/Silver/Blanco
1/2 oz Calvados
1 oz fresh lemon juice
1/2 oz simple syrup
1 bar spoon Green Chartreuse
1 bar spoon Velvet Falernum
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters

Method: Add all ingredients to a shaking tin with ice. Shake until chilled and diluted, about 10 - 15 seconds. Strain into a chilled coupe. Garnish with a twist of lemon. Sip, savor, and drink the sunshine in.

#ANGOSTURA #ANGOSTURAbitters #Tequila #Mixology #Cocktails #Recipe #Cheers #HappyHour

If you’re looking for ways to use your ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters, here’s a twofer. Both classics in their own regard, The Espresso Martini and The Widow’s Kiss – fortunately, classics never go out of style. They’re each as elegant as they are refreshing.

Espresso Martini:
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters
1 ½ oz Vodka
1 oz Espresso Coffee
2/3 oz coffee liqueur
1 pinch salt (optional)

Garnish: Lemon zest twist (discarded) plus float three coffee beans on the surface

Method: Shake all ingredients with ice and fine strain into chilled glass

Widow's Kiss Recipe:
3 dashes ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters
1 ½ oz Cognac
½ oz Benedictine
½ oz Green Chartreuse

Method: Add ingredients to mixing glass. Add ice, and stir for 12 seconds. Strain into chilled Nick and Nora glass.
#ANGOSTURA #ANGOSTURAbitters #Mixology #Cocktails #Recipe #Cheers #HappyHour

National Daiquiri Day is best spent celebrating with ANGOSTURA® 1919. We're adding some summer flavor with notes of passionfruit. Tell us your favorite way to mix in a seasonal spin to this classic cocktail.

2 oz Angostura 1919 Rum
¾ oz fresh lime juice

3 dashes Angostura orange bitters
Add the rum, bitters, lime, syrup and ice.  Shake until well-chilled. Double-strain into a coupe glass. Garnish with a lime wheel.

ANGOSTURA® Cup
Ingredients
5 dashes ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters
2 ounces of a gin-based liqueur
1/2 ounce lemon juice
1/2 ounce raspberry syrup
2-3 cubes cucumber (muddled)
2 cucumber ribbons (garnish)
2 raspberries (garnish)
Top with sparkling lemonade

Method:
Add cucumber and raspberry syrup to a cocktail shaker then muddle
Next add the gin-based liqueur and lemon juice and shake with ice
Add cucumber ribbon and ice to serving glass
Strain cocktail and top with sparkling lemonade
Add 5 dashes of ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters to the top, then garnish with remaining rolled cucumber ribbon and raspberries
